@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home";
}

<div class="card">
    <h1>Welcome to WireStimulus</h1>
    <p>
        A comprehensive demonstration of <strong>Stimulus.AspNetCore</strong> - bringing the power of 
        <a href="https://stimulus.hotwired.dev/" target="_blank">Hotwired Stimulus</a> to ASP.NET Core applications.
    </p>
    
    <div class="alert alert-info">
        <strong>What is Stimulus?</strong>
        <p>Stimulus is a modest JavaScript framework for the HTML you already have. It pairs beautifully with 
        server-side rendering and provides just enough structure to keep your JavaScript organized and maintainable.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Examples</h2>
    <p>Explore the following interactive examples showcasing different Stimulus controllers with ASP.NET Core Tag Helpers:</p>
</div>

<div class="examples-grid">
    <a href="/Dropdown" class="example-card">
        <h3>🎯 Dropdown Controller</h3>
        <p>Click to toggle dropdown menus with window click detection for auto-closing.</p>
    </a>

    <a href="/Clipboard" class="example-card">
        <h3>📋 Clipboard Controller</h3>
        <p>Copy text to clipboard with visual feedback and customizable success duration.</p>
    </a>

    <a href="/Counter" class="example-card">
        <h3>🔢 Counter Controller</h3>
        <p>Increment, decrement, and reset counter values with configurable step values.</p>
    </a>

    <a href="/Form" class="example-card">
        <h3>✅ Form Validation Controller</h3>
        <p>Real-time form validation with custom rules and instant feedback.</p>
    </a>

    <a href="/Slideshow" class="example-card">
        <h3>🖼️ Slideshow Controller</h3>
        <p>Image carousel with navigation controls, indicators, and autoplay support.</p>
    </a>
</div>

<div class="card" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
    <h2>Key Features</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Tag Helpers</strong> - Use familiar Razor syntax with <code>stimulus-controller</code>, <code>stimulus-action</code>, etc.</li>
        <li><strong>HTML Helpers</strong> - Alternative HTML Helper methods for generating Stimulus attributes</li>
        <li><strong>Type Safety</strong> - Strongly-typed attributes with IntelliSense support</li>
        <li><strong>Easy Integration</strong> - Works seamlessly with existing ASP.NET Core MVC applications</li>
    </ul>
</div>
